**Module:** relay
**Depends on:** Relay-A9 (architecture), Relay-A8 (profession_tokens data)

## Overview

Detailed component design for replacing the inline Cost Breakdown pie chart panel (RelayView.vue lines ~326–370) with a multi-color segmented progress bar in the budget bar area (lines ~96–113), including a hover tooltip showing a horizontal bar chart of per-agent token usage.

## Verified Code Context

| Item | Location | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Budget bar area | `RelayView.vue:96-113` | `.budget-bar-container` with mono `.budget-fill` — **replace this** |
| Cost Breakdown panel | `RelayView.vue:326-370` | Inline SVG donut chart + `.pie-legend` — **delete this** |
| `pieSlices` computed | `RelayView.vue` script | Inline pie chart data — **delete** |
| `professionColors` map | `RelayView.vue` script | HSL color map for pie — **delete** (replaced by `PROFESSION_PALETTE` in composable) |
| `_professionTokens` | `useRelay.ts:16` | Singleton `ref<Record<string, number>>({})` — **data source, already exists** |
| `professionTokens` | `useRelay.ts` return | Exposed from `useRelay()` — **wire into composable** |
| `budgetUsedPercent` | `useRelay.ts:~104` | Existing computed — **can keep or replace** |
| Cost panel CSS | `RelayView.vue` style | `.cost-panel`, `.cost-chart`, `.pie-*` rules — **delete** |
| **No `CostBreakdownChart.vue`** | — | Pie chart is inline in RelayView — **no separate file to delete** |

